aspguidp.gui.component

Class AutocompletePopupAssistant

  • java.lang.Object
    • aspguidp.gui.component.AutocompletePopupAssistant

  • public class AutocompletePopupAssistant
extends java.lang.Object
    Assistant class which provides static methods to set up a autocomplete popup. Autocomplete popups are used to display suggestion in a popup below input fields in the input components of the application (InputElementController).

    This class provides methods to load the popup content from the .fxml file into a node, initialize the popup content controller (AutocompletePopupController) and setup a handler to manage the popup visibility and position.

        public static void initializeAutocompletePopup(javafx.scene.control.TextField inputField,
                                               SuggestionService suggestionService)
        Initialize an autocomplete popup for the given input field. The displayed suggestions in the popup are gathered from the given suggestion service.
        Parameters:
        inputField - input field for which content of the autocomplete popup is initialized

      • initializeAutocompletePopup

        public static void initializeAutocompletePopup(javafx.scene.control.TextField inputField,
                                               SuggestionService suggestionService,
                                               java.util.List<java.lang.String> excludedSuggestions)
        Initialize an autocomplete popup for the given input field. The displayed suggestions in the popup are gathered from the given suggestion service. Suggestions in the given list of excluded suggestions are not displayed in the popup.
        Parameters:
        inputField - input field for which content of the autocomplete popup is initialized
        suggestionService - service which is used to gather suggestions for the current input field content
        excludedSuggestions - list of suggestions which should not be displayed in the popup window
